This is an unofficual example of a build on Ubuntu 20.
For this example we'll be using the ninja build tools.
It has not been formally tested yet and welcomes your feedback.

Sources:

https://github.com/prusa3d/PrusaSlicer/issues/3099#issuecomment-548268917 and other comments from this thread

### Install dependencies

```
sudo apt update
sudo apt -y install git libgtk2.0-dev libudev-dev ninja-build
```

### Clone repo

```
git clone https://github.com/prusa3d/PrusaSlicer
cd PrusaSlicer
```

### [optional] If you don't want to build bleeding-edge, checkout version

```
git checkout "v2.4.0-alpha.1"
```

### Build

#### A] Build normally

```
cd deps
mkdir build
cd build
cmake -G Ninja ..
ninja
cd ../..
mkdir build
cd build
cmake .. -G Ninja -DSLIC3R_STATIC=1 -DCMAKE_PREFIX_PATH="$PWD/../deps/build/destdir/usr/local"
ninja
```

#### B] Build with GTK3

```
cd deps
mkdir build
cd build
cmake -G Ninja .. -DDEP_WX_GTK3=ON
ninja
cd ../..
mkdir build
cd build
cmake .. -G Ninja -DSLIC3R_STATIC=1 -DCMAKE_PREFIX_PATH="$PWD/../deps/build/destdir/usr/local" -DSLIC3R_GTK=3
ninja
```

### Running the built executable

```
cd src
./prusa-slicer
```
